President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Kansas, providing federal assistance to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The assistance is for the areas affected by severe storms, straight-line winds, and flooding that occurred from July 22 to July 27, 2017. The federal funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. David G. Samaniego has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made based on requested assessments and the extent of damage. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.